hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant equations for a rotating compact object of period $P$ and mass $M$:
   - Light cylinder radius: $$R_L=\frac{c}{\Omega}\,,\quad \Omega=\frac{2\pi}{P}\,.$$
   - Schwarzschild radius: $$R_S=\frac{2GM}{c^2}\,.$$
2. Express $R_L$ in terms of $P$:
   $$R_L=\frac{c}{\Omega}
   =\frac{c}{2\pi/P}
   =\frac{cP}{2\pi}\,.$$
3. Impose the critical condition $R_L=R_S$:
   $$\frac{cP}{2\pi}=\frac{2GM}{c^2}\,.$$
4. Solve for the critical period $P_{\rm crit}$:
   $$P_{\rm crit}
   =\frac{2\pi}{c}\,\frac{2GM}{c^2}
   =\frac{4\pi GM}{c^3}\,.$$
